subSubSection.paragraph:
Male terminalia (Fig. 
3
): blackish, darker on upper lobe of cercus, visible part of phallus yellowish. Epandrium and hypandrium fused, rather rounded in lateral view, bearing scattered small dark setae. Left and right lamellae separated by unpigmented densely micropilose membrane. Cercus fused with epandrium + hypandrium, forked, upper lobe of cercus slightly curved and pointed. Subepandrial process sharply projecting anteriorly, rather slim and straight. Phallus apically slender, yellowish.
